HEADWORD: Bethel
<hw>Beth"el</hw> <pr>(b⟦ecr⟧th"⟦ecr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>b⟦emac⟧th-el</ets> house of God.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A place of worship; a hallowed spot.</def>
<rj><au>S. F. Adams.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A chapel for dissenters.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A house of worship for seamen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bethink</ent>⟦br⟧
